transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling customer service, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi, my name is Reginald Warren.

Speaker 1: I had an order put in, but I want to check the package.

Speaker 2: Because I think it's been over five business days already.

Speaker 1: Okay, let me have a look.

Speaker 2: What's your name and birthday?

Speaker 1: My name is Reginald Joe Warren, Reginald J. Warren.

Speaker 2: My date of birth is 03-31-1936.

Speaker 1: Doctor is changing to 25 milligrams.

Speaker 2: Confirm with patient.

Speaker 1: It says the doctor is changing you to 25 milligrams.

Speaker 2: Huh?

Speaker 1: It says the doctor was trying to change you to 25 milligrams.

Speaker 2: Let me see why.

Speaker 1: Why? Why would he want to change me?

Speaker 2: I have no idea. Let me see.

Speaker 1: Okay, so I just want to make sure this is everything.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: He paid for 100 milligrams.

Speaker 2: Needs max 25 milligrams.

Speaker 1: Don't smell me.

Speaker 2: What I said to you was,

Speaker 1: Do you have the only thing I can write for you?

Speaker 2: If you didn't pick any one of the drugs?

Speaker 1: Are you okay with that?

Speaker 2: I'm not going to put you on any type of monthly prescription.

Speaker 1: I said to you,

Speaker 2: I can't write you.

Speaker 1: It says that the doctor gave you 25 milligrams before.

Speaker 2: It was not a prescription for 25 milligrams.

Speaker 1: I never got a previous prescription from you.

Speaker 2: Huh?

Speaker 1: I never got a previous prescription from you anywhere.

Speaker 2: It says in 2023.

Speaker 1: I never received that.

Speaker 2: Oh, you didn't.

Speaker 1: I'm so confused.

Speaker 2: No, no, no, no, no.

Speaker 1: Oh, because they didn't properly change it.

Speaker 2: I don't know what's going on.

Speaker 1: I wanted 100 milligrams.

Speaker 2: No, no, no, no.

Speaker 1: It says, let me tell you what it says.

Speaker 2: It says the doctor said,

Speaker 1: Due to your CKD-5,

Speaker 2: I'm not sure what that is,

Speaker 1: But it says due to your CKD-5,

Speaker 2: The only thing I can write for you is 25 milligram tablets.

Speaker 1: Are you okay with that?

Speaker 2: And it says back in 2023 you agreed to it.

Speaker 1: And then the doctor was supposed to change your medication.

Speaker 2: So you submitted 400 milligrams again,

Speaker 1: But this doctor as well is saying the same thing,

Speaker 2: That they can only give you 25 milligram tablets.

Speaker 1: So when am I going to get the tablets anyway?

Speaker 2: You're going to get them.

Speaker 1: I just need to let them know that you're okay with getting 25 milligrams,

Speaker 2: And I'm going to have the doctor change it.

Speaker 1: I mean, I agreed on the phone with the lady for 100 milligram tablets.

Speaker 2: Okay, give me one second.
